- Christian, I told you to come here
- Rosa!

356
00:34:24,761 --> 00:34:26,784
- Hi Ramon
- I told you to come here!

357
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:30,712
Leave him, it's ok.
Are you good or bad?

358
00:34:33,137 --> 00:34:36,041
- Bad.
- Then we will get along fine

359
00:34:36,768 --> 00:34:38,561
- I'm Julia
- I'm Rosa, nice to meet you

360
00:34:39,143 --> 00:34:40,488
I'm sorry to have interrupted you

361
00:34:42,264 --> 00:34:43,664
I'll go for a while and leave you alone

362
00:34:49,567 --> 00:34:51,999
- How are you?
- Fine

363
00:34:52,439 --> 00:34:56,091
I hope you are not here to give me some of
those reasons to live you always bring

364
00:34:56,552 --> 00:34:59,501
No. No way.
Well, I don't know...

365
00:35:00,212 --> 00:35:02,950
I wanted to see you.
And wanted you to meet my sons

366
00:35:03,213 --> 00:35:04,126
That's better

367
00:35:06,036 --> 00:35:10,460
Christian, behave yourself.
We are not at home.

368
00:35:11,308 --> 00:35:13,564
This is Samuel.
Sami, say hello

369
00:35:15,171 --> 00:35:16,116
Hi, Sami.

370
00:35:19,236 --> 00:35:22,619
- Why are you in bed?
- Because he can't move, I already explained it to you

371
00:35:23,754 --> 00:35:25,068
Is it true you can't feel a thing?

372
00:35:29,321 --> 00:35:33,186
What happens to you now?
Are you hot?

373
00:35:34,067 --> 00:35:36,250
Is just that with this weather you never know.

374
00:35:36,913 --> 00:35:44,113
We are on strike because there's been a month
since they paid us. So it's like Sunday for us

375
00:35:44,465 --> 00:35:48,912
I made the breakfast, we took the bus
and we came to see you

376
00:35:52,145 --> 00:35:53,335
- What happened?
- Nothing

377
00:35:56,895 --> 00:35:58,735
Samuel, why are you crying now?

378
00:36:01,343 --> 00:36:02,015
Manuela...

379
00:36:05,918 --> 00:36:07,951
What do you think about all this?
Tell me the truth

380
00:36:09,103 --> 00:36:10,486
What do I think about what?

381
00:36:14,071 --> 00:36:15,869
That your brother in law wants to die

382
00:36:17,565 --> 00:36:18,805
That�s what he wants

383
00:36:20,749 --> 00:36:21,533
Ok, but...

384
00:36:24,494 --> 00:36:28,708
...but you. What would you want?
What would you prefer?

385
00:36:30,245 --> 00:36:32,493
What I prefer has no importance

386
00:36:33,339 --> 00:36:36,227
Ramon wants to die.
Everything is quite clear for me

387
00:36:39,092 --> 00:36:42,404
- Would you like to see a thing?
- A thing?

388
00:36:43,546 --> 00:36:44,738
Yes, come

389
00:36:50,655 --> 00:36:53,503
- Christian, leave that alone
- Leave me alone!

390
00:36:54,447 --> 00:36:56,278
I'm going to leave your ass like
a ripe tomato

391
00:37:18,701 --> 00:37:20,148
Almost all of them are poems

392
00:37:24,204 --> 00:37:25,725
I never threw anything away

393
00:37:26,381 --> 00:37:29,996
I couldn't do it.
It takes a lot of effort for him to write them

394
00:37:30,155 --> 00:37:32,013
And his handwriting...
Look...

395
00:37:35,723 --> 00:37:37,787
I never saw such a beautiful handwriting

396
00:37:42,402 --> 00:37:45,802
- Ok. I'll be downstairs
- Manuela

397
00:37:47,251 --> 00:37:49,026
Is going to take me a while to read all of this

398
00:37:49,274 --> 00:37:53,386
- Would you mind telling Ramon that...
- That you went to the beach

399
00:37:54,865 --> 00:37:57,489
- ...to take a walk
- Thanks

400
00:38:05,633 --> 00:38:08,673
Of course it is the first and the
last time I bring you here

401
00:38:09,513 --> 00:38:11,440
- But mom, that guy is faking it
- The last time!

402
00:38:19,399 --> 00:38:22,145
- Did she tell you when would she be back?
- Just to take a walk

403
00:38:22,921 --> 00:38:24,513
That way you can take a nap

404
00:38:26,538 --> 00:38:29,376
- You can't complain
- Why?

405
00:38:31,463 --> 00:38:35,416
Not a minute passes by that a woman
comes into this house. Are you building a harem?

406
00:38:38,519 --> 00:38:42,230
Manuela, you know I�m only married to one

407
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:45,071
Yes, with Death

408
00:39:02,028 --> 00:39:03,908
- Do you want anything else?
- No

409
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:28,848
They told me you were here.
And I came flying

410
00:43:31,947 --> 00:43:33,098
Manuela...

411
00:43:44,051 --> 00:43:45,057
Hi

412
00:43:46,657 --> 00:43:48,480
How was the walk?

413
00:43:50,201 --> 00:43:51,489
I've been reading Ramon

414
00:43:53,144 --> 00:43:55,169
I've been reading all that you have done.

415
00:43:57,688 --> 00:43:58,920
You know what?

416
00:44:02,767 --> 00:44:03,938
What you have written...

417
00:44:06,321 --> 00:44:07,393
