00:51:21,902 --> 00:51:25,562
Manuela kept the whole month covering me
so next year doesn't catch me off guard

491
00:51:26,206 --> 00:51:31,829
Javi keeps fighting with his grandpa and sometimes
I make up little chores so they spend more time together

492
00:51:32,061 --> 00:51:36,356
This month some friends came to visit.
Some of them have been doing it for 25 years

493
00:51:36,805 --> 00:51:38,701
and that keeps surprising me

494
00:51:39,125 --> 00:51:41,061
They enjoy telling me their stories

495
00:51:42,387 --> 00:51:44,451
Do you remember Rosa?
The girl from the conserve factory.

496
00:51:44,796 --> 00:51:46,500
I think she found here some kind of refuge

497
00:51:46,843 --> 00:51:50,930
The other day she wanted to help Manuela to
change my clothes, and they ended up arguing

498
00:51:51,211 --> 00:51:56,969
I proved again that when you depend on someone
for everything, you lose your privacy

499
00:51:57,283 --> 00:52:03,683
Well...I hope to keep my little kingdom in order
until you can cheer me up with your presence

500
00:52:04,194 --> 00:52:04,970
A big hug.

501
00:52:13,393 --> 00:52:14,081
What's going on?

502
00:52:15,488 --> 00:52:16,641
Let's see. What does it say here?

503
00:52:19,014 --> 00:52:21,597
"No es asi la vida que va" (The life that goes is not like that)

504
00:52:21,758 --> 00:52:25,710
No sir. It has to say
"No es as� la vida. Qu� va" (Life is not like that. No way)

505
00:52:25,750 --> 00:52:28,649
- No
- Yes. And that "Qu�" has accent

506
00:52:28,905 --> 00:52:31,889
That "Qu�" has accent. Do you see it?
Right there.

507
00:52:33,216 --> 00:52:36,081
"Death is my friend,"
where's the colon?

508
00:52:37,209 --> 00:52:39,425
What are they teaching you in school?

509
00:52:40,272 --> 00:52:42,095
You have to pay attention to what I give you

510
00:52:43,063 --> 00:52:44,788
Even your grandpa would do it better

511
00:52:46,231 --> 00:52:49,302
Look Javi, if this is the way you are going to help
I rather you didn't do it, ok?

512
00:52:49,726 --> 00:52:51,296
Because you make me work twice

513
00:52:54,871 --> 00:52:56,839
Give me the stick.
Give me the stick

514
00:52:58,128 --> 00:53:00,430
Put a little more attention, ok?

515
00:53:11,718 --> 00:53:13,949
- Javi, what happened?
- Nothing

516
00:53:31,796 --> 00:53:34,707
Dear Ramon...please forgive me for taking so
long in answering your letter

517
00:53:35,450 --> 00:53:40,946
But the doctors have limited me the use of the computer
and in general, any activity that doesn't make me use my legs

518
00:53:41,913 --> 00:53:45,665
They assure me that I�ll be able to walk again
but they say that I shouldn't continue with your case

519
00:53:47,529 --> 00:53:50,121
In the physical therapy room there's a huge window

520
00:53:51,208 --> 00:53:55,449
Sometimes I imagine that I go through it and fly,
like you, over Barcelona

521
00:53:56,088 --> 00:54:00,009
I reach the sea and keep flying until I can only
see that endless line of water

522
00:54:01,360 --> 00:54:07,304
And think, foolish me, that if you do the same
from Corunna, maybe you'll go around the world again

523
00:54:07,655 --> 00:54:10,831
And we end up finding each other in
some part of the planet

524
00:54:12,951 --> 00:54:16,303
I identify with you when you mention
the lack of freedom and privacy

525
00:54:17,262 --> 00:54:21,235
I try to bear with it, mainly for my husband
that takes care of me with much dedication

526
00:54:22,134 --> 00:54:24,901
But at the same time, I refuse to fall
into this inertia

527
00:54:25,350 --> 00:54:29,746
where I just can be grateful for what is given because
I have no other choice but to accept it

528
00:54:29,878 --> 00:54:31,797
I wish I�ll be able to see you in a couple of months

529
00:54:32,029 --> 00:54:34,085
And I keep my promise of helping you
with the book

530
00:54:34,478 --> 00:54:38,988
Until then receive the thanks and
a hug from a very good friend

531
00:54:42,871 --> 00:54:47,502
I knew this could happen, I knew it.
We are going to have to try again

532
00:54:48,006 --> 00:54:50,670
No Mark, how can you say
that we have to try again?

533
00:55:02,098 --> 00:55:04,065
As if justice is so swift in
this country

534
00:55:07,803 --> 00:55:10,508
No. And now it is me the one
that has to tell him

535
00:55:28,277 --> 00:55:35,038
The demand of the tetraplegic Ramon Sampedro requesting the euthanasia
was rejected yesterday by the tribunals due to defects in its form

536
00:55:35,305 --> 00:55:38,909
The sentence says that the judicial process
should have been started in Corunna

537
00:55:39,493 --> 00:55:42,494
where he resides, and not in Barcelona

538
00:55:42,948 --> 00:55:49,162
Many voices have been raised due to this case
among them is priest's Francisco de Galdar

539
00:55:49,418 --> 00:55:50,692
tetraplegic like Ramon

540
00:55:51,276 --> 00:55:54,626
Ramon says he doesn't want to
live anymore, but I wonder

541
00:55:55,395 --> 00:56:03,057
isn't it possible that Ramon is asking of society,
of all of us, some kind of attention

542
00:56:03,474 --> 00:56:04,713
What is he talking about?

543
00:56:05,322 --> 00:56:10,841
Maybe is that the people that surround him doesn't
provide the love or support that he needs

544
00:56:11,649 --> 00:56:12,505
That moron

545
00:56:13,313 --> 00:56:16,632
Couldn�t it be possible that what Ramon is
asking is for more love?

546
00:56:17,393 --> 00:56:24,620
I would really like to talk to him and convince him
that there are many reasons to keep on living

547
00:56:25,687 --> 00:56:27,135
Aren't you going to school?

548
00:56:36,846 --> 00:56:38,279
I hope you are happy now!

549
00:56:39,726 --> 00:56:41,110
Our whole family humiliated
on television

550
00:56:43,847 --> 00:56:47,302
But keep it up, keep it up.
Until our faces fall out of embarrassment

551
00:56:48,541 --> 00:56:50,445
And you dad? Aren't you going to tell him anything?

552
00:56:50,861 --> 00:56:54,249
Don't involve dad in this.
Whatever you have to tell me, do it and be done with it

553
00:57:03,095 --> 00:57:06,236
I'm going to tell you something Ramon.
I am the older brother

554
00:57:06,308 --> 00:57:08,328
Listen to me, listen to me for a moment

555
00:57:08,419 --> 00:57:10,444
What if you have an accident tomorrow
and you die?

556
00:57:14,140 --> 00:57:15,010
Have you thought about it?

557
00:57:16,019 --> 00:57:19,618
What would happen to me?
I would have to take care of the family, right?

558
00:57:20,443 --> 00:57:24,674
Of your wife, your son, dad...
With that miserable pension of mine

559
00:57:25,826 --> 00:57:29,497
If I stay alive, I�ll make
things a lot more difficult

560
00:57:31,042 --> 00:57:34,978
I'm going to tell you something Ramon.
I am the older brother

561
00:57:35,233 --> 00:57:39,896
I am the older here. And while I�m alive,
no one is getting killed here

562
00:57:40,447 --> 00:57:43,440
No one in this house is getting killed.
Put that in your head, Ramon

563
00:57:43,863 --> 00:57:44,807
No one!

564
00:58:12,094 --> 00:58:15,852
- Ok, son. I'll leave
- See you tomorrow dad

565
00:58:35,435 --> 00:58:36,467
I'll go

566
00:58:39,451 --> 00:58:40,995
Hi Manuela, I came to see Ramon

567
00:58:41,487 --> 00:58:43,378
But, do you know what time it is?

568
00:58:43,626 --> 00:58:46,545
I know. I couldn't come sooner.
I'll explain it to Ramon

569
00:58:47,066 --> 00:58:50,748
I don't think he's in the mood of visits.
He had a bad day

570
00:58:51,306 --> 00:58:53,265
Why don't you come tomorrow?
Or the day after?

571
00:58:53,641 --> 00:58:54,513
It's important

572
00:58:55,860 --> 00:58:57,468
The conserve factory is closing

573
00:58:59,075 --> 00:59:02,099
That things are not going well.
That there's no money to pay us

574
00:59:02,827 --> 00:59:04,066
And that we are fired

575
00:59:04,386 --> 00:59:06,428
There's no right, damn it!

576
00:59:06,463 --> 00:59:07,391
There's no right.

577
00:59:11,536 --> 00:59:13,767
- Forgive me Ramon
- I have nothing to forgive

578
00:59:14,886 --> 00:59:18,870
Cry all you want.
I wish I could stand up and give you a hug

579
00:59:22,616 --> 00:59:24,830
Now that I had started to save some money

580
00:59:26,030 --> 00:59:28,862
I wanted to buy you a telescope
for the day of the Wise Men

581
00:59:29,182 --> 00:59:30,901
You don't have to buy me anything, Rosa

582
00:59:31,110 --> 00:59:33,126
I will get really mad if you spend one cent on me

583
00:59:33,493 --> 00:59:34,877
But I really wanted to

584
00:59:38,405 --> 00:59:41,365
- I wanted to give you something
- But why do you have to give me anything?

585
00:59:42,188 --> 00:59:44,796
Because you game me a lot Ramon,
you have no idea

586
00:59:52,283 --> 00:59:54,762
No man has never been so kind to me
as you have been

587
00:59:55,595 --> 00:59:57,051
Was it that bad?

588
01:00:06,218 --> 01:00:07,842
Now, I don't complicate things

589
01:00:08,546 --> 01:00:11,874
Now I know that the problem must be me, right

590
01:00:13,849 --> 01:00:15,738
That men doesn't like me or something

591
01:00:16,330 --> 01:00:18,864
What do you say, Rosa?
How is that even possible?

592
01:00:20,969 --> 01:00:23,696
Wasn't that what you told me when I came
here the first time?

593
01:00:24,521 --> 01:00:25,792
Frustrated woman, you said

594
01:00:27,872 --> 01:00:33,928
Yes, yes. If I called you that then,
now I call you strong and brave

595
01:00:34,623 --> 01:00:39,306
and kind and beautiful. And I call an imbecile
to those who can't see it

596
01:00:44,375 --> 01:00:45,502
Rosa, please stop it.

597
01:00:45,973 --> 01:00:48,445
You make me feel like a priest and
I hate them enough already

598
01:00:48,718 --> 01:00:50,821
Sit over here, come on sit.

599
01:00:56,645 --> 01:00:59,032
And leave my hand alone, you know I can't feel it

600
01:01:01,708 --> 01:01:03,596
My son says you are faking it.

601
01:01:11,698 --> 01:01:14,955
But you do feel your face, right?

602
01:01:28,433 --> 01:01:35,993
I wish I could help you.
I would do anything to help you.

603
01:01:36,273 --> 01:01:38,289
You would help me?

604
01:01:38,537 --> 01:01:39,761
Yes

605
01:01:41,544 --> 01:01:46,464
Don't worry. I have it all planned
so that no one ends up in jail

606
01:01:47,439 --> 01:01:49,990
I have some friends that are willing to help

607
01:01:51,512 --> 01:01:54,695
I only need one more.
Someone brave, like you

608
01:01:54,984 --> 01:01:58,448
No.

609
01:01:59,967 --> 01:02:01,519
Help you heal...

610
01:02:03,694 --> 01:02:05,438
not die

611
01:02:19,132 --> 01:02:22,699
Come un guys, let's go.

612
01:02:28,492 --> 01:02:30,060
Are you holding him?

613
01:02:37,507 --> 01:02:39,307
He won't fit through here

614
01:02:47,541 --> 01:02:50,658
Ramon says that he understands the situation
but that he won't come down

615
01:02:56,929 --> 01:02:59,465
Ok. It doesn't matter.
Brother Andres

616
01:03:04,688 --> 01:03:07,960
Go upstairs and tell Ramon

617
01:03:16,295 --> 01:03:21,942
...and since we are inside eternity.
Life doesn't belong to us...

618
01:03:22,391 --> 01:03:27,872
and we take to ridiculous extremes the
bourgeois definition of private property

619
01:03:30,237 --> 01:03:31,157
You are killing me

620
01:03:31,798 --> 01:03:35,421
But if Church was the first one in
secularize the private property

621
01:03:37,405 --> 01:03:38,608
- I can't tell him that
- How come?

622
01:03:39,239 --> 01:03:40,487
Should I tell him that?

623
01:03:43,807 --> 01:03:51,626
Freedom to choose my beliefs...no, his beliefs
and decide over his life

624
01:03:53,214 --> 01:03:54,766
Ok, now you tell him

625
01:03:57,446 --> 01:04:00,974
Why does the Church keep with such passion
that posture of terror of death?

626
01:04:01,573 --> 01:04:04,269
Because it knows that it would lose
a great amount of its customers

627
01:04:04,493 --> 01:04:06,701
if people lose their fear to the
Great Beyond

628
01:04:07,493 --> 01:04:13,789
He reminds you that according to the polls,
67% of the Spanish are in favor of euthanasia

629
01:04:14,069 --> 01:04:18,100
Very well, very well. Now you tell him
that moral issues are not resolved through polls

630
01:04:18,620 --> 01:04:23,003
Because most of the German people was
also in favor of Hitler

631
01:04:23,268 --> 01:04:25,612
Now he is going to compare me to Hitler.
That is very rude

632
01:04:26,203 --> 01:04:27,075
No, not that

633
01:04:29,563 --> 01:04:31,859
Ask him what does Hitler has to do with anything

634
01:04:32,863 --> 01:04:38,298
No wait...
Padre Francisco, do you hear me?

635
01:04:39,722 --> 01:04:41,818
Yes. Ramon I can hear you

636
01:04:42,433 --> 01:04:44,346
Why do you mix pears with apples?

637
01:04:45,361 --> 01:04:47,553
I hope you didn't come here to do demagoguery.

638
01:04:48,017 --> 01:04:50,256
Because you Jesuits know a lot about that.

639
01:04:50,585 --> 01:04:52,282
No, no. Of course not.

640
01:04:52,456 --> 01:04:55,512
But since you bring up demagoguery, my dear Ramon.

641
01:04:57,087 --> 01:05:01,479
Don't you think that what's really demagogic is
to say "Death with dignity"

642
01:05:02,975 --> 01:05:07,094
Why don't you leave the euphemisms aside and
call things by its name, with all its rawness

643
01:05:07,179 --> 01:05:08,679
"I take my life" and that's it...

644
01:05:09,758 --> 01:05:15,607
It keeps surprising me your interest in my life,
when the Institution that you represent

645
01:05:16,350 --> 01:05:23,029
accepts the death penalty and condemned for centuries
to the bonfire those who didn't think in the right way

646
01:05:23,133 --> 01:05:25,496
Now it is you the one doing demagoguery

647
01:05:25,597 --> 01:05:30,269
Yes of course, but leaving the euphemisms aside, as you say
that's what you would have done with me, right?

648
01:05:30,781 --> 01:05:32,140
Burn me alive

649
01:05:32,884 --> 01:05:34,812
Burn me for defending my freedom

650
01:05:35,798 --> 01:05:36,923
Ramon, my friend...

651
01:05:37,452 --> 01:05:38,131
Friend?

652
01:05:38,445 --> 01:05:41,475
Ramon, my friend. A freedom that
eliminates life is not freedom

653
01:05:41,892 --> 01:05:43,868
And a life that eliminates freedom is not life either

654
01:05:45,011 --> 01:05:47,620
Don't call me friend!
And leave me alone

655
01:05:53,594 --> 01:05:54,740
Come on. Let's go

656
01:05:59,947 --> 01:06:05,813
You...you that look like kind people,
give this man reasons to live

657
01:06:07,633 --> 01:06:12,888
Prove to him that life is not only
moving your arms and running around

658
01:06:13,160 --> 01:06:17,820
or kicking a ball.
Damn it! Life is something else, really

659
01:06:18,852 --> 01:06:22,292
Life is so much more.
Hear it from me.

660
01:06:25,595 --> 01:06:28,051
And what do you want us to do?

661
01:06:28,299 --> 01:06:30,347
That we gag him so he doesn't talk?

662
01:06:31,163 --> 01:06:33,746
Or that we put him to sleep with a
rattle like a little kid

663
01:06:36,874 --> 01:06:41,226
Look. you appeared on TV and
something that I can't take out of my head

664
01:06:41,897 --> 01:06:42,890
Manuela, leave it alone

665
01:06:43,312 --> 01:06:46,568
You said that Ramon's family didn't
give him enough love...

666
01:06:47,103 --> 01:06:51,105
you should know that in this house no one
stopped loving Ramon for one single day

667
01:06:51,552 --> 01:06:52,392
Not one day

668
01:06:54,345 --> 01:06:59,512
I've been looking after him for many years
and I love him like a son

669
01:07:03,822 --> 01:07:05,799
I don't know which one of you is right

670
01:07:06,606 --> 01:07:11,219
And I don't know if it's true what you say
about life belonging to God and not to us

671
01:07:13,344 --> 01:07:15,174
but I do know one thing

672
01:07:16,190 --> 01:07:18,541
you have a very big mouth

673
01:07:38,788 --> 01:07:42,163
Rosa, I told you that is not
necessary. I already shaved Ramon

674
01:07:42,396 --> 01:07:44,370
Yes, yes. But I know a better way

675
01:07:48,642 --> 01:07:49,619
Where do you have the soap?

676
01:07:52,683 --> 01:07:53,490
They're here

677
01:08:07,394 --> 01:08:10,456
I don't feel anything.
Are you sure there's a child in there?

678
01:08:10,816 --> 01:08:12,153
7 months old, darling

679
01:08:13,401 --> 01:08:15,621
- Well, he's not moving
- You're the one that doesn't move

680
01:08:15,776 --> 01:08:17,472
- Now, now, now
- See

681
01:08:18,650 --> 01:08:21,680
- He's happy to see you
- How are you going to call him?

682
01:08:21,976 --> 01:08:23,816
We still don't know

683
01:08:24,855 --> 01:08:29,254
Well, call him Ramon and that way one day
when he asks why, you can tell him my story

684
01:08:30,270 --> 01:08:31,574
Is better if you tell him

685
01:08:37,622 --> 01:08:40,182
There's someone else who will
be really happy to see you

686
01:08:45,806 --> 01:08:49,181
- No, no. Not like that
- Grandpa, shut up

687
01:08:59,436 --> 01:09:02,939
- How come you didn't say anything?
- We wanted to surprise you

688
01:09:03,588 --> 01:09:05,963
This a great Wise Men's day present

689
01:09:06,135 --> 01:09:08,370
I'm going to open the windows,
it's really hot in here

690
01:09:08,675 --> 01:09:10,867
We better get out and
leave you alone for a while

691
01:09:20,329 --> 01:09:21,578
How are you sailor?

692
01:09:28,097 --> 01:09:29,905
- Do you drink coffee Mark?
- Yes, please

693
01:09:30,313 --> 01:09:32,954
- How are you Rosa?
- Fine

694
01:09:33,289 --> 01:09:35,481
Ramon told me that you had found a new job

695
01:09:36,194 --> 01:09:38,144
Yes, caring for some elderly people

696
01:09:40,590 --> 01:09:42,335
Does that woman is going to stay long?

697
01:09:43,608 --> 01:09:46,503
A couple of weeks, depending on how
long the book takes

698
01:09:47,976 --> 01:09:52,015
Well, I guess I won't be able to shave him.
See you some other time

699
01:09:52,303 --> 01:09:53,341
Bye Rosa

700
01:09:54,647 --> 01:09:57,702
Ok, the judges have their hands
tied because of the legislation

701
01:09:58,885 --> 01:10:01,265
We are going to try to
obtain a statement

702
01:10:01,841 --> 01:10:05,361
where we recommend to the government
changes to the penal code

703
01:10:05,713 --> 01:10:08,577
- The government?
- The government is there to serve us, Javi

704
01:10:08,874 --> 01:10:10,057
Your uncle is more important

705
01:10:10,769 --> 01:10:13,824
The jury will not dare agree with us,
we already know that

706
01:10:14,834 --> 01:10:17,176
But we cannot fail on the
regional audience

707
01:10:20,911 --> 01:10:22,975
Javier, help me with the cows

708
01:10:31,807 --> 01:10:35,302
We have to convince the judges that
Ramon is complete sane and lucid

709
01:10:36,318 --> 01:10:39,293
It would help us a lot
if he would make a declaration

710
01:10:39,797 --> 01:10:43,333
Manuela, we have to take Ramon
out of the house

711
01:10:46,253 --> 01:10:48,205
Can you tell me what were
you doing in there?

712
01:10:49,432 --> 01:10:51,565
Do you know what are they talking about?
What they want?

713
01:10:52,149 --> 01:10:53,900
And what do I do?
Lock myself up in the room?

714
01:10:54,099 --> 01:10:55,693
Do you understand what they really want?

715
01:10:58,396 --> 01:11:00,164
What happens if he wins the trial?

716
01:11:01,123 --> 01:11:07,170
Your uncle gets injected and dies, like a dog.
And you never see him again

717
01:11:08,028 --> 01:11:09,346
You will never see him again, Javier

718
01:11:10,039 --> 01:11:11,398
Or do you think death is so great?

719
01:11:12,806 --> 01:11:14,662
Please use your head

720
01:11:15,119 --> 01:11:17,045
Death is a very serious thing, you hear me?

721
01:11:17,709 --> 01:11:20,593
- Your uncle dies and you won't see him again.
- Leave me alone

722
01:11:27,966 --> 01:11:31,033
Is not that he doesn't feel like it, he
just doesn't want to use the chair

723
01:11:32,685 --> 01:11:36,180
Taking him out of the house once or twice
a year is an accomplishment

724
01:11:36,420 --> 01:11:40,540
Well, this one has to be one of those times.
It is very important that Ramon takes this trip.

725
01:11:42,541 --> 01:11:43,868
And when would that be?

726
01:11:45,307 --> 01:11:48,012
I estimate that the trial will take place in the spring

727
01:11:48,204 --> 01:11:50,499
So we still have time to propose it to him.

728
01:11:51,930 --> 01:11:55,234
There's only one thing worse than the death of a son

729
01:11:56,706 --> 01:11:58,394
and that is he wanting to die

730
01:12:25,960 --> 01:12:27,832
Well, let's get to work

731
01:13:17,922 --> 01:13:24,049
"...get inside of you, eternally,
my seducer lover, beloved sea"

732
01:13:27,065 --> 01:13:29,009
Can you really smell the sea from here?

733
01:13:29,234 --> 01:13:31,784
Yes, and sometimes in the morning if there's wind

734
01:13:33,416 --> 01:13:37,056
and the window is open,
I can smell it as if I was there

735
01:13:38,432 --> 01:13:39,672
You have a very good nose

736
01:13:39,889 --> 01:13:44,416
Smells are probably what cause me
more intense sensations

737
01:13:46,256 --> 01:13:47,670
More fantasies

738
01:13:51,238 --> 01:13:53,126
...your smell, for example.

739
01:13:56,510 --> 01:13:58,151
My smell

740
01:13:59,734 --> 01:14:04,606
Yes, is the first thing I imagine when
I day dream about you

741
01:14:07,137 --> 01:14:08,193
Really?

742
01:14:10,081 --> 01:14:13,082
- And what are those dreams about?
- Just things

743
01:14:15,672 --> 01:14:17,873
They all have one thing in common...

744
01:14:19,015 --> 01:14:21,443
In all of them I can move...

745
01:14:23,494 --> 01:14:30,778
and I stand up and travel wherever
I imagine you are at that moment

746
01:14:33,039 --> 01:14:35,558
And if I imagine that you are here, for example

747
01:14:38,190 --> 01:14:40,383
I just get close to you

748
01:14:42,782 --> 01:14:45,461
And do what I have been
wishing to do so many times

749
01:14:45,997 --> 01:14:51,093
Then your smell becomes
stronger and I get dizzy

750
01:14:53,013 --> 01:14:58,571
I can feel your heart beat
then I feel your hands

751
01:15:01,148 --> 01:15:05,332
And then I lose my mind...
I lose my mind

752
01:15:37,904 --> 01:15:38,994
Is the water ok?

753
01:16:01,038 --> 01:16:02,206
Julia...

754
01:16:04,510 --> 01:16:06,173
Julia, are you awake?

755
01:16:08,798 --> 01:16:09,581
Yes

756
01:16:12,092 --> 01:16:12,997
I can't sleep

757
01:16:15,988 --> 01:16:17,060
Why is that

758
01:16:19,004 --> 01:16:21,956
I have an itching in one leg,
can you come and scratch it?

759
01:16:23,108 --> 01:16:23,955
...the leg

760
01:16:43,603 --> 01:16:45,115
I brought him some "filloas"

761
01:16:46,738 --> 01:16:48,602
- I know he likes them - Rosa,
please listen -I made them

762
01:16:50,217 --> 01:16:55,007
I've told you that you don't have to cook him
anything, or bathe him or shave him. Nothing

763
01:16:55,103 --> 01:16:56,679
I take care of Ramon.
Get it?

764
01:16:58,887 --> 01:17:02,606
- Ok, then I want to hear it from him
- No, he already told me

765
01:17:04,159 --> 01:17:05,982
Besides, he is very busy now.

766
01:17:07,871 --> 01:17:09,334
Is he with her?

767
01:17:15,885 --> 01:17:19,950
I wish I was a lawyer too.
But of course...

768
01:17:28,636 --> 01:17:32,596
- Don't cry Rosa, don't cry
- If you don't want to see me, please tell me

769
01:17:33,260 --> 01:17:36,124
- Of course I want to see you
- It doesn't look that way

770
01:17:36,547 --> 01:17:37,787
Really, what are you...

771
01:17:40,394 --> 01:17:42,283
Rosa...
Rosa...

772
01:17:43,995 --> 01:17:45,018
She hung up

773
01:17:48,115 --> 01:17:51,721
Do you mind dialing the number again
and giving me a minute alone

774
01:18:04,336 --> 01:18:06,744
What's going on between you two, Ramon?

775
01:18:11,037 --> 01:18:12,333
But Julia...

776
01:18:14,628 --> 01:18:16,564
Why would I need to explain anything to you?

777
01:18:17,497 --> 01:18:21,859
I don't understand why you answer me like that,
because then I don't know what I�m doing here.

778
01:18:24,479 --> 01:18:27,886
Unless of course, you think that there's
nothing happening here

779
01:18:28,080 --> 01:18:30,327
The kiss you gave me yesterday meant nothing?

780
01:18:33,886 --> 01:18:35,126
Look at you

781
01:18:37,351 --> 01:18:38,918
Look at you sitting there

782
01:18:40,822 --> 01:18:42,278
Look at you

783
01:18:43,429 --> 01:18:45,494
And now look at me

784
01:18:48,045 --> 01:18:49,783
Where are we going Julia?

785
01:18:51,685 --> 01:18:53,181
Look at us

786
01:18:54,644 --> 01:18:56,189
I haven't finished

787
01:18:58,340 --> 01:18:59,876
What do you think?

788
01:19:00,804 --> 01:19:02,922
That I don't think about what happened to me?

789
01:19:04,084 --> 01:19:06,930
Of course, I think about it. Frequently.

790
01:19:09,220 --> 01:19:11,651
Every single day. It's like a nightmare.

791
01:19:14,722 --> 01:19:18,474
And I know that it will only get worse and worse
until I end up like a vegetable

792
01:19:19,010 --> 01:19:22,730
So I have reached a conclusion and I rather...

793
01:19:32,048 --> 01:19:33,330
I'm going to do it Ramon.

794
01:19:37,304 --> 01:19:39,748
I'm going to take my own life

795
01:19:48,684 --> 01:19:54,403
But before I do it, if you want to, my love...

796
01:19:57,187 --> 01:19:59,634
I would like to help you.

797
01:20:04,745 --> 01:20:06,288
Leave together...

798
01:20:12,665 --> 01:20:16,425
You don't say anything?
You didn't expect this.

799
01:20:20,248 --> 01:20:21,584
When?

800
01:20:24,008 --> 01:20:28,631
I don't know. We are almost done
with the book and...

801
01:20:31,103 --> 01:20:38,886
I'll go to Barcelona and look for an editor
so you can publish it.

802
01:20:39,279 --> 01:20:47,646
And then I�ll come back with the first copy.
That same day, Ramon. That same day.

803
01:20:49,516 --> 01:20:53,227
Listen to me, in the worst case scenario
we would win the public support.

804
01:20:53,468 --> 01:20:55,907
If the verdict is negative the
discussion will be more heated

805
01:20:56,293 --> 01:21:00,362
- Don't be stupid...I can't
understand... - Are you ok? - Yes, Yes

806
01:21:01,803 --> 01:21:03,250
News, what news?

807
01:21:05,267 --> 01:21:09,825
Mark, please be careful. It's ok, it's ok.
What happened Ramon?

808
01:21:10,012 --> 01:21:11,292
We are here.

809
01:21:13,555 --> 01:21:18,788
I understand Ramon, I understand.
But that doesn't matter

810
01:21:19,035 --> 01:21:26,491
Listen to me, if no one takes this step. If everyone hides their
heads and doesn't even try to confront the state, the judges...

811
01:21:41,280 --> 01:21:44,528
And what do we do now Manuela?
I mean, with the trip to Corunna.

812
01:21:44,960 --> 01:21:46,833
Do I go there and waste my time?

813
01:21:47,168 --> 01:21:49,145
Knowing that they won't listen to me.

814
01:21:49,608 --> 01:22:01,199
Well, I think that today it is a waste of time but
maybe tomorrow it could be useful for someone else

815
01:22:11,950 --> 01:22:14,121
Ok. Let's go and see those judges in the face

816
01:22:19,508 --> 01:22:22,444
- Javi, where is the chair
- The chair?

817
01:22:23,445 --> 01:22:25,150
I don't know, it's probably in the back.

818
01:22:25,484 --> 01:22:31,148
Well, I want you to take it out and clean it up. Then bring
grandpa and I�ll explain. We are going to make some changes

819
01:22:33,235 --> 01:22:34,963
Are going to put a motor?

820
01:22:34,987 --> 01:22:38,868
- You have to cut here and here
- Let the back move, right?

821
01:22:39,156 --> 01:22:47,388
You have to cut these pipes down here and then join them
with bolts so they move as hinges. Are you getting this?

822
01:22:48,162 --> 01:22:50,324
- Yes, yes
- And you dad?

823
01:22:50,515 --> 01:22:54,915
Your going to be lying down son.
You might fall sleep at the trial

824
01:22:55,083 --> 01:22:57,892
Is not like they're saying anything interesting, dad.

825
01:23:15,713 --> 01:23:17,241
Die to Live

826
01:23:19,489 --> 01:23:21,747
LETTERS FROM HELL

827
01:23:22,298 --> 01:23:24,438
You should put a pillow here
to support my head

828
01:23:24,590 --> 01:23:27,370
In case I fall backwards and break my neck

829
01:23:27,602 --> 01:23:33,129
Hey, Javi. Do you get it? Break
my neck... Break my neck...

830
01:23:47,072 --> 01:23:48,808
Grandpa

831
01:23:49,576 --> 01:23:52,832
Look, if you're going to help me like that,
is better if you do nothing

832
01:24:11,645 --> 01:24:15,085
- Am I tying you too tight?
- You're asking me?

833
01:24:22,604 --> 01:24:25,965
Wait a moment please.
Ramon

834
01:24:26,204 --> 01:24:28,805
Manuela, please.
As if I don't look ridiculous enough

835
01:24:29,092 --> 01:24:30,844
Better this than catching a cold

836
01:24:34,540 --> 01:24:36,651
And don't you dare, taking it off

837
01:24:42,242 --> 01:24:43,882
You are Ramon Sampedro, right?

838
01:24:45,083 --> 01:24:48,050
I really wished it was me the
one to take you.

839
01:25:50,071 --> 01:25:54,504
Living is a right,
not an obligation!

840
01:25:54,505 --> 01:25:59,476
- Look at all the people here
- Who did we kill, eh?

841
01:26:00,426 --> 01:26:04,882
Ramon, do you feel alone because you
are the only Spanish to have requested euthanasia?

842
01:26:05,162 --> 01:26:11,922
Yes, well, the first one in requesting it in a public manner.
But this has been happening for many years.

843
01:26:12,130 --> 01:26:14,257
What do you expect from the judges?
What are you going to tell them?

844
01:26:15,401 --> 01:26:20,880
I just want to tell them that
I�m completely sane and lucid

845
01:26:22,638 --> 01:26:24,069
Silence

846
01:26:29,613 --> 01:26:30,789
Can we talk later?

847
01:26:31,564 --> 01:26:32,677
Silence, please

848
01:26:34,971 --> 01:26:38,763
In a state declared as lay and that recognizes
the right to the private property

849
01:26:38,931 --> 01:26:43,899
and which constitution expresses also the right
not to suffer tortures or degrading treatments

850
01:26:44,451 --> 01:26:48,651
is correct to say, that whomever sees his position as
degrading, as in Ramon Sampedro's case,

851
01:26:49,561 --> 01:26:51,746
should be able to decide over his own life

852
01:26:52,075 --> 01:26:57,154
in fact, no one that attempts suicide
and survives is judged afterwards

853
01:26:58,338 --> 01:27:03,033
but...
when you need the help of someone else

854
01:27:04,033 --> 01:27:07,617
to die with dignity, then the state interferes with
the freedom of the people and tells them

855
01:27:07,808 --> 01:27:10,713
that the life they are living is not theirs,
that they can't make decisions about it

856
01:27:10,970 --> 01:27:15,008
This, Your Honor, can only be done based on
metaphysical beliefs, or religious

857
01:27:16,416 --> 01:27:18,975
In a state, I repeat...

858
01:27:20,216 --> 01:27:22,071
that is declared lay

859
01:27:23,270 --> 01:27:28,015
Your Honor, I ask for a legal answer,
but above all, rational

860
01:27:28,759 --> 01:27:30,310
and human

861
01:27:32,646 --> 01:27:38,740
And now, with your permission,
Ramon Sampedro would like to read something

862
01:27:40,110 --> 01:27:41,717
Overruled

863
01:27:42,157 --> 01:27:46,158
My client want to address you directly so you
hear from his own voice...

864
01:27:46,389 --> 01:27:49,028
You know perfectly well the process

865
01:27:49,644 --> 01:27:52,165
Of course I know it, I know it perfectly

866
01:27:53,180 --> 01:27:57,492
But I didn't know that it was so irrelevant
for you to give three minutes of your time

867
01:27:57,539 --> 01:27:58,227
Three...

868
01:27:59,468 --> 01:28:01,715
To listen to a man that has been waiting
for 28 years

869
01:28:01,892 --> 01:28:04,020
If you want to change the process...

870
01:28:04,323 --> 01:28:05,675
change the laws

871
01:28:06,892 --> 01:28:08,635
Yes, of course.
I know that already.

872
01:28:09,962 --> 01:28:11,771
This case is ready for a sentence.

873
01:28:25,210 --> 01:28:28,657
Well...I knew you were not going
to take it seriously.

874
01:28:29,484 --> 01:28:34,080
That's what all men do. Laugh at me.
You were not going to be different

875
01:28:34,337 --> 01:28:38,776
Rosa, forgive me. Is just that lately
a little of everything happens to me

876
01:28:40,512 --> 01:28:42,079
- And...I�m a little overwhelmed.
- Why?

877
01:28:42,790 --> 01:28:45,224
Is not allowed to fall in love
with a tetraplegic or what?

878
01:28:45,399 --> 01:28:46,600
Is it that weird?

879
01:28:48,206 --> 01:28:54,447
Well, maybe we should clear up some things.
Specially if we are talking about something as complex as love.

880
01:28:54,670 --> 01:28:56,439
- Complex?
- Yes Rosa, complex.

881
01:28:56,943 --> 01:29:03,646
No matter how much you tell me that you love me,
I will never be sure of how real is your love

882
01:29:03,925 --> 01:29:09,433
or if it's just an idealization of a man you wanted
to find but couldn't or didn't last.

883
01:29:09,605 --> 01:29:13,317
But what are you talking about Ramon?
Don't try to confuse me

884
01:29:13,516 --> 01:29:17,924
Either you love or you don't.
You can't rationalize love

885
01:29:21,766 --> 01:29:25,340
Well, if that's the case, what do you want me to do?
You want me to move in with you?

886
01:29:26,030 --> 01:29:28,493
For me is enough to know that
I can visit you from time to time

887
01:29:28,782 --> 01:29:31,301
Of course you can.
Of course you can

888
01:29:32,887 --> 01:29:34,861
Yes, but for how long?

889
01:29:36,309 --> 01:29:39,772
Rosa. You wouldn't ask me
to stay alive for you, right?

890
01:29:41,157 --> 01:29:42,884
What if I told you that...

891
01:29:47,444 --> 01:29:49,316
that you give me strength to live Ramon

892
01:29:49,692 --> 01:29:52,563
Wait wait. Stop this thing for a moment

893
01:29:53,635 --> 01:29:54,875
Sit over there.

894
01:29:58,923 --> 01:30:03,811
- Let's see. Do you love your children?
- Of course I do.

895
01:30:04,811 --> 01:30:06,850
Well, there you have the strength to live

896
01:30:07,481 --> 01:30:10,033
Don't give me that responsibility Rosa

897
01:30:10,258 --> 01:30:14,689
Is that what you call love?
Keep me here against my will?

898
01:30:15,537 --> 01:30:16,736
Look...

899
01:30:17,904 --> 01:30:22,464
The person that really loves me is
the one that will help me die.

900
01:30:24,200 --> 01:30:26,158
That is love, Rosa

901
01:30:31,807 --> 01:30:35,895
Dear Julia...yesterday I received the sentence
of the provincial audience

902
01:30:36,607 --> 01:30:42,699
the judges understand that I want to die, but
remind me that to help me, would be punishable by law

903
01:30:43,222 --> 01:30:46,118
In other times, this would have affected me a lot

904
01:30:46,470 --> 01:30:51,047
Pushing me into that alley without exit where
days and nights never end

905
01:30:51,925 --> 01:30:56,820
But now I feel that everything is rushing by
and that the publication of the book will happen any day now

906
01:30:58,221 --> 01:31:01,448
And with it you will return Julia.
My Juliet...

907
01:31:02,140 --> 01:31:05,228
It will be the sweetest death that I could ever imagine

908
01:31:05,436 --> 01:31:07,677
It will be love, pure and shared

909
01:31:08,100 --> 01:31:12,596
And it will be the return to balance.
Finally to balance

910
01:31:13,451 --> 01:31:14,891
A kiss, my dear friend

911
01:32:12,057 --> 01:32:13,436
Ok, see you later

912
01:32:23,540 --> 01:32:24,812
Should I open it?

913
01:32:28,956 --> 01:32:30,484
Is the book!

914
01:32:32,593 --> 01:32:35,410
Look, is the book.
You are on the cover

915
01:32:42,022 --> 01:32:43,804
It smells great

916
01:32:50,481 --> 01:32:51,650
Is for you

917
01:32:55,634 --> 01:32:56,945
I'm going to show it to mom

918
01:33:27,485 --> 01:33:35,541
Why...why...
why can't I be happy with this life?

919
01:33:35,717 --> 01:33:37,750
I'm going to give you a tranquilizer

920
01:33:37,838 --> 01:33:41,366
Why do I want to die?
Why do I want to die?

921
01:33:52,436 --> 01:33:53,685
Give me two more Manuela.

922
01:33:54,317 --> 01:33:56,524
Manuela, for crying out loud, two more
pills are not going to kill me

923
01:33:56,866 --> 01:33:57,995
Give me two more

924
01:34:04,673 --> 01:34:05,964
You'll feel better soon

925
01:34:48,862 --> 01:34:52,054
- How do you feel?
- Fine

926
01:34:53,493 --> 01:34:54,639
What time is it?

927
01:34:54,901 --> 01:34:57,633
11:00 am. I didn't want to wake you up today

928
01:35:00,069 --> 01:35:02,365
The girl from Boiro has called three times already

929
01:35:03,500 --> 01:35:04,868
What did she want?

930
01:35:05,612 --> 01:35:08,388
She says she has to talk to you about
something important

931
01:35:08,995 --> 01:35:13,915
- For her it is always important
- Dial the number for me please

932
01:35:15,067 --> 01:35:17,762
Are you going to call her?
Why don't you wait for her to call back?

933
01:35:17,939 --> 01:35:22,050
But she can barely pay her phone bill.
Dial the number please

934
01:35:24,707 --> 01:35:27,890
Of course Ramon.
You always so kind

935
01:35:34,570 --> 01:35:36,897
- Ramon?
- What's going Rosa?

936
01:35:38,208 --> 01:35:40,136
I need to see you. I have to talk to you

937
01:35:40,553 --> 01:35:44,522
- You said I should call you before visiting you
- Yes. Did something happened?

938
01:35:45,560 --> 01:35:47,152
Can I come now?

939
01:35:48,887 --> 01:35:54,219
Look Ramon, you said you had a plan or something

940
01:35:55,810 --> 01:36:00,394
That you had figured out a way of doing what you want to do,
if the judges decided against you

941
01:36:00,570 --> 01:36:02,297
Yes, Rosa, but I already asked you to
forgive me, right?

942
01:36:02,603 --> 01:36:03,882
I told you to forget about it

943
01:36:04,249 --> 01:36:05,754
Yes.
But I can't

944
01:36:05,969 --> 01:36:07,249
I can't, you know

945
01:36:07,881 --> 01:36:14,488
Because last month the audience said no.
And you are still thinking about doing it

946
01:36:14,689 --> 01:36:17,888
Is that what worries you?
That I get my way?

947
01:36:18,977 --> 01:36:22,001
- So, are you going to do it?
- Is not that easy, Rosa. But don't worry

948
01:36:22,768 --> 01:36:24,625
You will be the last person to find out.

949
01:36:32,608 --> 01:36:33,815
Ramon...

950
01:36:35,431 --> 01:36:41,951
Is that I realized...
I understood what you said in Corunna.

951
01:36:43,102 --> 01:36:46,398
"The person that really loves me will
be the one to help me"

952
01:36:46,782 --> 01:36:49,486
I'm completely sure about what I feel Ramon

953
01:36:50,598 --> 01:36:52,406
I love you

954
01:36:56,380 --> 01:36:58,269
Do you want me to help you?

955
01:37:01,340 --> 01:37:02,661
Rosa...

956
